'''Molytex''' was a strong military-grade material.<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Star by Star">''[[The New Jedi Order: Star by Star]]''</ref>

==Characteristics==
Commonly used in [[Blaster/Legends|blast]]-proof vests, [[Armor/Legends|armor]], and [[techstaff]]s, molytex was notable for creating [[Laminanium/Legends|laminanium]] by alternating layers of molytex and [[quantum fiber]]. This same alternating method of layering molytex and quantum fiber could also be used to make flexible and lightweight molytex armor, such as [[armored jumpsuit]]s which used molytex liners, and was distinct from laminanium.<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Star by Star">''[[The New Jedi Order: Star by Star]]''</ref>

Molytex armor granted the same impenetrability and durability as [[Laminanium/Legends|laminanium]], but not the self-regenerating properties.<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Star by Star">''[[The New Jedi Order: Star by Star]]''</ref> The material was capable of withstanding considerable kinetic force, and even [[Nang hul|thud bug]] impacts were reduced to a flinch and deep bruising as opposed to broken bones and lacerations.<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Star by Star">''[[The New Jedi Order: Star by Star]]''</ref> Likewise, molytex liner could withstand tremendous amounts of heat, being capable of reducing the damage of a [[magma pebble]] to thumb sized divots rather than gaping holes, and were also highly resistant to laceration, being able to shrug off [[voxyn]] claws as well as that of [[razor bug]]s with small rips and tears, though it could be be cleanly punctured by [[amphistaff]]s.<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Star by Star">''[[The New Jedi Order: Star by Star]]''</ref>

